Package aima.core.search.framework.qsearch

Class QueueSearch

  • java.lang.Object
    • aima.core.search.framework.qsearch.QueueSearch
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    BidirectionalSearch, GraphSearch, GraphSearchBFS, GraphSearchReducedFrontier, TreeSearch
    public abstract class QueueSearch
extends java.lang.Object
    Base class for queue-based search implementations, especially for TreeSearch, GraphSearch, and BidirectionalSearch. It provides a template method for controlling search execution and defines primitive methods encapsulating frontier access. Tree search implementations will implement frontier access straight-forward. Graph search implementations will add node filtering mechanisms to avoid that nodes of already explored states are selected for expansion.
    Author:
    Ravi Mohan, Ciaran O'Reilly, Mike Stampone, Ruediger Lunde

    • Method Detail

      • findNode

        public Node findNode​(Problem problem,
                     java.util.Queue<Node> frontier)
        Receives a problem and a queue implementing the search strategy and computes a node referencing a goal state, if such a state was found. This template method provides a base for tree and graph search implementations. It can be customized by overriding some primitive operations, especially addToFrontier(Node), removeFromFrontier(), and isFrontierEmpty().
        Parameters:
        problem - the search problem
        frontier - the data structure for nodes that are waiting to be expanded
        Returns:
        a node referencing a goal state, if the goal was found, otherwise null;
